#. Tag: title
#: definitions.docbook:2
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Uvod"

#. Tag: para
#: definitions.docbook:3
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In project management, terms may be used in different ways in different "
"programs or different companies or project types. Looking at more exhaustive "
"project management glossaries, one will find alternative definitions for "
"most terms."
msgstr ""
"Pri vodenju projektov se izrazi lahko uporabljajo na različne načine v "
"različnih programih ali različnih podjetjih ali vrstah projektov. Če "
"pogledamo izčrpnejše glosarje projektnega vodenja, boste našli alternativne "
"definicije za večino izrazov."

#. Tag: para
#: definitions.docbook:5
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This list defines how certain terms are used in <guilabel>Plan</guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"Ta seznam določa, kako se določeni izrazi uporabljajo v <guilabel>Planu</"
"guilabel>."

#. Tag: title
#: definitions.docbook:8
#, no-c-format
msgid "Terms"
msgstr "Pogoji"

#. Tag: emphasis
#: definitions.docbook:10
#, no-c-format
msgid "Account"
msgstr "Račun"

#. Tag: para
#: definitions.docbook:12
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An account is used in a <emphasis>Cost Breakdown Structure</emphasis> (<link "
"linkend=\"cbs\">CBS</link>) to represent a place where cost from <link "
"linkend=\"task\">tasks</link> or <link linkend=\"resource\">resources</link> "
"can be aggregated."
msgstr ""
"Račun se uporablja v <emphasis>Strukturi razčlenitve stroškov</emphasis> "
"(<link linkend=\"cbs\">CBS</link>), da predstavlja mesto, kjer stroški iz "
"<link linkend=\"task\">nalog</link > ali <link linkend=\"resource\">vire</"
"link> je mogoče združiti."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: definitions.docbook:15
#, no-c-format
msgid "ACWP"
msgstr "ACWP"

#. Tag: link
#: definitions.docbook:17
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<link linkend=\"Actual-Cost-of-Work-Performed\">Actual Cost of Work "
"Performed</link>"
msgstr ""
"<link linkend=\"Actual-Cost-of-Work-Performed\">Dejanski stroški "
"opravljenega dela</link>"

#. Tag: emphasis
#: definitions.docbook:20
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis role=\"bold\">Actual Cost of Work Performed</emphasis>"
msgstr "<emphasis role=\"bold\">Dejanski stroški opravljenega dela</emphasis>"

#. Tag: para
#: definitions.docbook:22
#, no-c-format
msgid "The actual cost (or effort) that has been performed."
msgstr "Dejanski stroški (ali napor), ki je bil opravljen."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: definitions.docbook:25
#, no-c-format
msgid "Allocation"
msgstr "Dodelitev"

#. Tag: para
#: definitions.docbook:27
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Tasks are allocated to <link linkend=\"resource\">Resources</link> during "
"the planning stage of the project. The actual assignment is done during "
"scheduling. Note that assignment is not guaranteed as the resource may not "
"be available."
msgstr ""
"Naloge so v fazi načrtovanja projekta dodeljene <link linkend=\"resource"
"\">Virom</link>. Dejanska dodelitev se opravi med razporejanjem. "
"Upoštevajte, da dodelitev ni zagotovljena, ker vir morda ni na voljo."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: definitions.docbook:30
#, no-c-format
msgid "Assignment"
msgstr "Dodelitev"

#. Tag: para
#: definitions.docbook:32
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Tasks are assigned to <link linkend=\"resource\">Resources</link> during "
"scheduling."
msgstr ""
"Naloge so med razporejanjem dodeljene <link linkend=\"resource\">Virom</"
"link>."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: definitions.docbook:35
#, no-c-format
msgid "BCWS"
msgstr "BCWS"

#. Tag: link
#: definitions.docbook:37
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<link linkend=\"Budgeted-Cost-of-Work-Scheduled\">Budgeted Cost of Work "
"Scheduled</link>"
msgstr ""
"<link linkend=\"Budgeted-Cost-of-Work-Scheduled\">Načrtovani stroški "
"planiranega dela</link>"

#. Tag: emphasis
#: definitions.docbook:40
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis role=\"bold\">Budgeted Cost of Work Scheduled</emphasis>"
msgstr "<emphasis role=\"bold\">Načrtovani stroški planiranega dela</emphasis>"

#. Tag: para
#: definitions.docbook:42
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The cost (or effort) that should have been used in order to reach the stated "
"progress."
msgstr ""
"Strošek (ali napor), ki bi ga morali porabiti, da bi dosegli navedeni "
"napredek."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: definitions.docbook:45
#, no-c-format
msgid "BCWP"
msgstr "BCWP"

#. Tag: link
#: definitions.docbook:47
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<link linkend=\"Budgeted-Cost-of-Work-Performed\">Budgeted Cost of Work "
"Performed</link>"
msgstr ""
"<link linkend=\"Budgeted-Cost-of-Work-Performed\">Načrtovani stroški "
"opravljenega dela</link>"

#. Tag: emphasis
#: definitions.docbook:50
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis role=\"bold\">Budgeted Cost of Work Performed</emphasis>"
msgstr ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Načrtovani stroški opravljenega dela</emphasis>"

#. Tag: para
#: definitions.docbook:52
#, no-c-format
msgid "The cost (or effort) that has been performed."
msgstr "Strošek (ali napor), ki je bil opravljen."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: definitions.docbook:55
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>CBS</emphasis>"
msgstr "<emphasis>CBS</emphasis>"

#. Tag: link
#: definitions.docbook:57
#, no-c-format
msgid "Cost Breakdown Structure"
msgstr "Struktura razčlenitve stroškov"

#. Tag: emphasis
#: definitions.docbook:60
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>CPI</emphasis>"
msgstr "<emphasis>CPI</emphasis>"

#. Tag: para
#: definitions.docbook:62
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Is the <emphasis>Cost Performance Index</emphasis> and is equal to <link "
"linkend=\"bcwp\">BCWP</link>/<link linkend=\"acwp\">ACWP</link>. When this "
"index is below 1, means that you are over budget. If the index is greater "
"than 1 means that the costs are under budget."
msgstr ""
"Je <emphasis>indeks stroškovne uspešnosti</emphasis> in je enak <link "
"linkend=\"bcwp\">BCWP</link>/<link linkend=\"acwp\">ACWP</link>. Ko je ta "
"indeks pod 1, pomeni, da ste presegli načrt. Če je indeks večji od 1, "
"pomeni, da so stroški pod načrtovanimi."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: definitions.docbook:65
#, no-c-format
msgid "Cost Breakdown structure"
msgstr "Struktura razčlenitve stroškov"

#. Tag: para
#: definitions.docbook:67
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The CBS organizes <link linkend=\"account\">accounts</link> into a structure "
"to enable cost to be aggregated independent of the <link linkend=\"wbs"
"\">WBS</link> and <link linkend=\"rbs\">RBS</link>."
msgstr ""
"CBS organizira <link linkend=\"account\">račune</link> v strukturo, ki "
"omogoča združevanje stroškov neodvisno od <link linkend=\"wbs\">WBS</link> "
"in <link linkend=\"rbs\"> RBS</link>."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: definitions.docbook:70
#, no-c-format
msgid "Estimate"
msgstr "Ocena"

#. Tag: para
#: definitions.docbook:72
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The estimate is the expected amount of effort or time needed to complete a "
"<link linkend=\"task\">task</link>."
msgstr ""
"Ocena je pričakovana količina napora ali časa, potrebnega za dokončanje "
"<link linkend=\"task\">naloge</link>."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: definitions.docbook:75
#, no-c-format
msgid "Milestone"
msgstr "Mejnik"

#. Tag: para
#: definitions.docbook:77
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A milestone is a <link linkend=\"task\">task</link> with an effort of 0.00h. "
"It is typically used to mark a major outcome, for example the completion of "
"a deliverable upon customer acceptance."
msgstr ""
"Mejnik je <link linkend=\"task\">naloga</link> z naporom 0,00 h. Običajno se "
"uporablja za označevanje pomembnega izida, na primer dokončanje končnega "
"izdelka po sprejemu stranke."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: definitions.docbook:80
#, no-c-format
msgid "PERT"
msgstr "PERT"

#. Tag: link
#: definitions.docbook:82
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<link linkend=\"Program-Evaluation-and-Review-Technique\">Program Evaluation "
"and Review Technique</link>"
msgstr ""
"<link linkend=\"Program-Evaluation-and-Review-Technique\">Tehnika "
"ocenjevanja in pregleda programa</link>"

#. Tag: emphasis
#: definitions.docbook:85
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Program Evaluation and Review Technique</emphasis>"
msgstr ""
"<emphasis role=\"bold\">Tehnika vrednotenja in pregleda programa</emphasis>"

#. Tag: para
#: definitions.docbook:87
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Program Evaluation and Review Technique is an enhancement to the "
"Critical Path Method. <link linkend=\"task\">Task</link> effort estimates in "
"CPM are point estimates, while <link linkend=\"task\">task</link> effort "
"estimates in PERT are computed by weighting the Optimistic, Most Likely, and "
"Pessimistic estimates (O+(4*M)+P)/6."
msgstr ""
"Tehnika vrednotenja in pregleda programa je izboljšava metode kritične poti. "
"Ocene napora <link linkend=\"task\">naloge</link> v CPM so točkovne ocene, "
"medtem ko so ocene napora <link linkend=\"task\">naloge</link> v PERT "
"izračunane s ponderiranjem Optimistične, Najverjetnejše in Pesimistične "
"ocene (O+(4*M)+P)/6."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: definitions.docbook:90
#, no-c-format
msgid "PERT Distribution"
msgstr "Distribucija PERT"

#. Tag: para
#: definitions.docbook:92
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A simplified way to calculate Expected estimate from Optimistic-, Most "
"Likely- and Pessimistic estimate."
msgstr ""
"Poenostavljen način za izračun pričakovane ocene iz optimistične, "
"najverjetnejše in pesimistične ocene."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: definitions.docbook:95
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>RBS</emphasis>"
msgstr "<emphasis>RBS</emphasis>"

#. Tag: link
#: definitions.docbook:97
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<link linkend=\"Resource-Breakdown-Structure\">Resource Breakdown Structure</"
"link>"
msgstr ""
"<link linkend=\"Resource-Breakdown-Structure\">Struktura razčlenitve virov</"
"link>"

#. Tag: emphasis
#: definitions.docbook:100
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis role=\"bold\">Resource Breakdown Structure</emphasis>"
msgstr "<emphasis role=\"bold\">Struktura razčlenitve virov</emphasis>"

#. Tag: para
#: definitions.docbook:102
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The RBS organizes resources into <link linkend=\"Resource-Group\">resource "
"groups</link>."
msgstr ""
"RBS organizira vire v <link linkend=\"Resource-Group\">skupine virov</link>."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: definitions.docbook:105
#, no-c-format
msgid "Resource"
msgstr "Vir"

#. Tag: para
#: definitions.docbook:107
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A resource can be of type <emphasis>Work</emphasis>, <emphasis>Material</"
"emphasis> or <emphasis>Team</emphasis>. A resource must always belong to a "
"<link linkend=\"Resource-Group\">Resource Group</link>."
msgstr ""
"Vir je lahko vrste <emphasis>Delo</emphasis>, <emphasis>Material</emphasis> "
"ali <emphasis>Ekipa</emphasis>. Vir mora vedno pripadati <link linkend="
"\"Resource-Group\">skupini virov</link>."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: definitions.docbook:110
#, no-c-format
msgid "Resource Group"
msgstr "Skupina virov"

#. Tag: para
#: definitions.docbook:112
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A resource group is used to group similar <link linkend=\"resource"
"\">resources</link>."
msgstr ""
"Skupina virov se uporablja za združevanje podobnih <link linkend=\"resource"
"\">virov</link>."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: definitions.docbook:115
#, no-c-format
msgid "Resource Team"
msgstr "Ekipa za vire"

#. Tag: para
#: definitions.docbook:117
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A <link linkend=\"resource\">resource</link> team is a resource that "
"consists of a number of other resources."
msgstr ""
"Ekipa za <link linkend=\"resource\">vir</link> je vir, ki je sestavljen iz "
"številnih drugih virov."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: definitions.docbook:120
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>SPI</emphasis>"
msgstr "<emphasis>SPI</emphasis>"

#. Tag: para
#: definitions.docbook:122
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Is the Schedule Performance Index and is equal to BCWP/BCWS. When this index "
"is below 1, means that you are behind schedule. If the index is greater than "
"1 means that you are ahead of the schedule."
msgstr ""
"Je indeks uspešnosti urnika in je enak BCWP/BCWS. Ko je ta indeks pod 1, "
"pomeni, da zaostajate za načrtom. Če je indeks večji od 1, pomeni, da "
"prehitevate načrt."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: definitions.docbook:125
#, no-c-format
msgid "Summary Task"
msgstr "Zbirna naloga"

#. Tag: para
#: definitions.docbook:127
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A Summary Task has subordinate Sub-Tasks, and rolls up information based on "
"the Sub-Tasks."
msgstr ""
"Naloga povzetka ima podrejene pod-naloge in zbira informacije na podlagi pod-"
"nalog."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: definitions.docbook:130
#, no-c-format
msgid "Task"
msgstr "Naloga"

#. Tag: para
#: definitions.docbook:132
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A Task is a unit of work. <link linkend=\"resource\">Resources</link> are "
"generally allocated at the Task level."
msgstr ""
"Naloga je enota dela. <link linkend=\"resource\">Viri</link> so običajno "
"dodeljeni na ravni naloge."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: definitions.docbook:135
#, no-c-format
msgid "vCard"
msgstr "vCard"

#. Tag: para
#: definitions.docbook:137
#, no-c-format
msgid "vCard is a file format standard for electronic business cards."
msgstr "vCard je standardna oblika datoteke za elektronske vizitke."

#. Tag: emphasis
#: definitions.docbook:140
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis>WBS</emphasis>"
msgstr "<emphasis>WBS</emphasis>"

#. Tag: link
#: definitions.docbook:142
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<link linkend=\"Work-Breakdown-Structure\">Work Breakdown Structure</link>"
msgstr ""
"<link linkend=\"Work-Breakdown-Structure\">Struktura razčlenitve dela</link>"

#. Tag: emphasis
#: definitions.docbook:145
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis role=\"bold\">Work Breakdown Structure</emphasis>"
msgstr "<emphasis role=\"bold\">Struktura razčlenitve dela</emphasis>"

#. Tag: para
#: definitions.docbook:147
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The WBS is used to break down large projects into manageable chunks to ease "
"planning and management."
msgstr ""
"WBS se uporablja za razčlenitev velikih projektov na obvladljive dele za "
"lažje načrtovanje in upravljanje."
